The paper discusses graphical navigation tools for the web, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). It also mentions techniques for adapting link presentation based on user characteristics, which could fall under natural language processing (cs.CL) or deep learning (cs.DL). Finally, the paper discusses criteria for comparing these tools, which could be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
